[2] Saudi Arabia, 13 new cases, 3 deaths - MOH 20 Apr 2014
Date: 20 Apr 2014
Source: Saudi MOH 20 Apr 2014
http://www.moh.gov.sa/CoronaNew/PressReleases/Pages/mediastatemenet-2014-04-20-001.aspx


MOH confirms 13 new cases of MERS-CoV infection - 20 Apr 2014
--------------------------
In the context of the work of epidemiological investigation and ongoing follow-up carried out by the Ministry of Health for the MERS-CoV, the Ministry announces the registration of 13 cases of the virus in the Kingdom.

The 1st is a 49 year old male resident in Jeddah who has passed away.
The 2nd is a 57 year old female citizen in Jeddah receiving intensive care treatment.
The 3rd is a 32 year old female resident in Jeddah in stable condition.
The 4th is a 53 year old male citizen in Jeddah in stable condition.
The 5th is a 54 year old citizen in Jeddah in stable condition.
The 6th is a 23 year old asymptomatic resident in Jeddah.
The 7th is a 37 year old male resident in Jeddah working in the health field in stable condition.

The 8th is a 69 year old female citizen in Riyadh, suffering from several chronic diseases, and is receiving intensive care treatment.
The 9th is an 88 year old male citizen in Riyadh, suffering from several chronic diseases, and receiving intensive care treatment.
The 10th is a 57 year old citizen in Riyadh suffering from several chronic diseases and in stable condition.
The 11th is a 41 year old male resident working in the health sector in Riyadh and is in stable condition.

The 12th is a 68 year old male citizen of the Najran region who had been suffering from several chronic diseases, and has passed away.

And the 13th is a 68 year old male citizen of the Medina area who had been suffering from several chronic diseases, and has passed away.

In this context, and in order from the Ministry of Health to provide all members of the community, the media and social networking guidelines of health and medical advice on HIV corona virus that causes AIDS Middle East, respiratory, and inform them of the developments around it, they invite everyone to access the link on the disease through the Ministry's website www.moh.gov.sa / Coronanew , or communicate via toll-free phone 8002494444 or 937 center or through a link saudimoh @ Twitter wishing for all health and safety.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The addition of these 13 new cases including 3 deaths raises the total number of laboratory confirmed cases of MERS-CoV in Saudi Arabia to 244 cases including 79 deaths, and will raise the global tally of laboratory confirmed MERS-CoV cases to above 300 cases. Of note, all but one of the cases reported today have signs of clinical disease ranging from stable (6 cases) to requiring intensive care (3 cases) or fatal (3 cases).

For a map of Saudi Arabia, see < https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2417384,131>. - Mod.MPP]

